<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2588862>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Apseudomorpha drummi sp. nov. holotype ovigerous female (UF Arthropoda 49366). A, dorsal view; B, enlargement of rostrum; C, enlargement of pleon and pleotelson, dorsal lateral view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm for A and 0.1 mm for B̅C" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2588862/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2588872>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Apseudomorpha drummi sp. nov. paratype male (UF Arthropoda 49369). A, cheliped, lateral view; B, enlargement of prolongation of propodus; C, enlargement of fixed finger and dactylus; D, cheliped, inner view; E, enlargement of simple and bipinnate spiniform setae; F, enlargement of bipinnate spiniform setae. Scale bars = 1.0 mm for A–C." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2588872/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2588864>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Apseudomorpha drummi sp. nov. paratype ovigerous female (UF Arthropoda 49370). A, antennule; B, antenna; C, labrum; D, left mandible; E, enlargement of left lacinia mobilis; F, right mandible; G, enlargement of incisor; H, enlargement of right lacinia mobilis; I, enlargement of right molar process; J, mandible palp. Scale bars = 0.1 mm" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2588864/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2588866>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Apseudomorpha drummi sp. nov. paratype ovigerous female (UF Arthropoda 49370). A, labium; B, maxillule; C, maxilla; D, enlargement of inner pinnate spiniform setae; E, enlargement of bipinnate sub-distal spiniform setae; F, trifurcateplumose spiniform setae; G, enlargement of bipinnate spiniform seta; H, enlargement of inner trifurcate-plumose spiniform setae; I, maxilliped; J, enlargement of setulate spiniform setae; K, endite. Scale bar = 0.1 mm" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2588866/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2588868>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Apseudomorpha drummi sp. nov. paratype ovigerous female (UF Arthropoda 49370). A, cheliped, lateral view; B, cheliped, inner view; C, enlargement of simple and bipinnate spiniform setae; D, enlargement of spiniform seta. Scale bar = 0.1 mm for A and B" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2588868/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2588870>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Apseudomorpha drummi sp. nov. paratype ovigerous female (UF Arthropoda 49370). A, pereopod-1, outer view; B, enlargement of bipinnate spiniform seta; C, merus to dactylus of pereopod-1, inner view; D, pereopod-2, outer view; E, merus to dactylus of pereopod-2, inner view; F, pereopod-3, outer view; G, merus to dactylus of pereopod-3, inner view; H, pereopod-4, outer view; I, carpus to dactylus of pereopod-4, inner view; J, enlargement of pectinate setae. Scale bar = 0.1 mm except for B and I" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2588870/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2588874>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Map showing the worldwide distribution of Apseudomorpha. A. albida (green circle); A. avicularia (magenta circle); A. drummi sp. nov. (red circle); A. fontainei (yellow circle); A. glebosa (cyan circle); A. hirsuta (cream circle); A. magdalenensis (orange circle); A. martinicana (purple circle); A. negoescuae (blue circle); A. oahuensis (dark green circle); A. ortizi (pink circle); A. timaruvia (brown circle); A. veleronis (black circle); A. vestafricana (grey circle). [Data from: Shiino (1951); Barnard (1914); Guţu (1987, 2006, 2007, 2009); Menzies (1953); Stebbing (1910); Miller (1940); Chilton (1882); this study]." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2588874/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

